Your code sample isn't quite right.<p>[read stdin] returns a string (not a list of strings), which is parsed as a list when you try to loop over it.  The parsing breaks the string into a list of words, so the second loop is redundant.  The parsing could fail if the input file isn't valid list syntax (unmatching {}'s).  [split _] makes it safe.<p><pre><code>    foreach word [split [read stdin]] {
        if [string match *ing $word] { puts $word }}
</code></pre>
I love Tcl too!  Tcl is a scripting language for C, Python is less-powerful version of Lisp.
